subproject.description: The project strengthens the enabling frameworks and capacities for managing the National Protected areas system in Zambia and recommends appropriate policy, regulatory and governance frameworks in order to provide new tools for public-private-community-civil society management partnerships. It also aims at strengthening and enhancing existing institutional capacities for improved protected areas monitoring and evaluation and business investment planning.
